<subSubSection id="C31F2DDDBF25FFDB7CE2FD37FC41DE62" pageId="18" pageNumber="429" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BBA7E56BF25FFDB7CE2FD37FC41DE62" blockId="18.[761,1348,608,1026]" pageId="18" pageNumber="429">
The taxonomic status of the Culpeo is still unresolved, despite a range of propositions for including it under 
<taxonomicName id="4C0505D5BF25FFDB7ADCFD69FAE0DE10" authorityName="C. E. H. Smith" authorityYear="1839" box="[1223,1339,761,790]" class="Mammalia" family="Canidae" genus="Dusicyon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="18" pageNumber="429" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Dusicyon</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0505D5BF25FFDB7CE7FCB1FC9FDE38" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[764,836,801,830]" class="Mammalia" family="Canidae" genus="Canis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="18" pageNumber="429" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Canis</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0505D5BF25FFDB7DBFFCB1FBC4DE38" authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1854" box="[932,1055,801,830]" class="Mammalia" family="Canidae" genus="Lycalopex" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="18" pageNumber="429" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Lycalopex</taxonomicName>
. Six subspecies are recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
